title: Release Jikken v0.6.0
body: Details can be found in the CHANGELOG.

title: JK-232: fix hash for Windows release
JK-163: Add support for HTTP Verbs being case insensitive
JK-20: Add support for injecting file data into JKT definition
Feature/jk 230
body: This updates the variable pattern matching to be the same as JavaScript and Bash string interpolation `${variable}` instead of the existing pattern `$variable$`. We're about to overhaul the documentation so this is a good time to make this type of change before it is used more widely.

title: refactored main entrypoint funtion
body:
Extracted templating to separate file.
Eliminated redundant command parsing
Removed passing CLI object through test executor.

title: adjust status messaging to change plurality based on number of tests
Feature/jk 143 adjust end messaging
body: This fixes both telemetry and status messaging for when exiting test execution early (due to configuration and a failure occurring)..

title: update package management files for new release
Feature/jk 138 fix telemetry cross platform
body: The original telemetry code had a module which failed to compile on MacOSX. We've removed that dependency any built our own mechanism on top of another library which does support MacOS along with Windows and Linux our three main platforms.

title: Feature/jk 135 ignore add params
body:
This fixes a bug with compare requests not properly handling ignore and add param definitions.
This also cleans up all outstanding warnings from clippy.

title: update readme with choco badge and instructions
Feature/jk 10 webapp telemetry
body: Initial telemetry support for the Jikken.io webapp. This is opt-in, as no telemetry will be sent unless a user provides an API key enabling the functionality.

title: update configuration handling, add support for user path config
body:
Add support for a home folder based configuration file.
Also refactored the code around configs to be a cleaner abstraction into a separate module.

title: Feature/jk 41 refactor code public mvp
body: Update module structure and overall coding style to match closer to newer idiomatic rust.

title: update windows package manager and installer versions
body:
This should have been done in the original PR for releasing v0.4.0
I've updated my version release runbook to not forget these steps in the future.

title: [JK-130] Fix issues with jk new command
body:
The `jk new` command was not properly inserting new lines into the output.
The output printer when using -o with `jk new` is using the wrong log macro.

title: [JK-129] clean-up logging adjusting verbose and trace messaging
